# FY Sell-In Data Product (Streamlit)

This project was re-engineered from an R Shiny application into a Python-based Streamlit data product, enabling better scalability, simplified deployment, and alignment with modern data engineering and analytics workflows.

## Overview

This application standardizes and automates sell-in performance analysis across fiscal years. It transforms raw transactional data into a reusable analytics layer with an interactive interface for business users.

## Problem Statement

Sell-in analysis is often fragmented across Excel files and manual reporting processes, resulting in:

- Inconsistent data definitions
- Limited visibility across fiscal periods
- Time-consuming manual aggregation
- Lack of scalable and reusable analytics tools

The original implementation in R Shiny faced limitations in deployment flexibility, dependency management, and integration with broader data workflows.

## Solution

This project introduces a lightweight data product that:

- Ingests structured CSV data
- Applies standardized transformation logic
- Generates consistent KPI outputs
- Provides an interactive interface for business users

The migration to Python + Streamlit improves portability and makes the solution easier to integrate with modern data stacks.

## Core Capabilities

- Monthly sell-in trend comparison across fiscal years
- Automated variance calculation (period-over-period)
- Brand-level aggregation and ranking
- Volume share calculation
- Structured output for downstream usage
- Downloadable dataset for further analysis

